Watford midfielder Abdoulaye Doucoure has revealed he’s wanted by Tottenham, Liverpool and Arsenal this summer. The 25-year-old former France U21 has had an excellent season for the Hornets under both Marco Silva and new boss Javi Gracia. Abdoulaye Doucoure was asked a guest on French media channel Telefoot: “The French media understands clubs like Tottenham, Liverpool and Arsenal are following you – what is the objective?” And he replied: “It’s true that these clubs are interested in me. But I am at Watford and my focus is on finishing the season well and to maintain their Premier League status. “After, when the club and I make the decision to make the next step, then that will have to be agreed but, for now, I am focused on Watford.” Doucoure has scored seven Premier League goals in 22 appearances this season, after joining Watford from Rennes in 2016. The post Arsenal, Liverpool And Tottenham Want Me- Abdoulaye Doucoure appeared first on 360Nobs.com. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 360Nobs.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.